        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Solve a system of linear equations, i.e., A*X = B, where X is unknown. For a square matrix A, this function is conceptually the same as X = inv(A)*B, but is done more efficiently. The number of rows in A and B must be the same. B can be either a column vector or a matrix. This function will also try to provide approximate solutions to under-determined as well as over-determined systems (non-square A matrices). </para>        </detaileddescription>
